      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Gollan-trained REVALENE (4) ran below expectations here last time off a solid first-up effort at Ipswich. He will be fitter again and has more to give. Has a low gate and 2kg claim and should be ready to fire. JEMELDI (5) was outgraded at Doomben 10 days ago but the form prior stacks right up for this. Won here this grade and trip and then went close in Open company at Ipswich. Draws inside and has winning claims. PENINSULA (6) went close here over 1000m in a 78 first-up, after a stable switch. Proven second-up and has more up his sleeve. Maps for a soft run and should be right in the finish. PANTELONE (1) resumes in easier with a handy 3kg claim. Has won fresh and owns a trial win on the inner track. He's likely to give a sight. HEROIC MISS (2) has been racing in much stronger and can't be ruled out 35 days freshened and with a tick over trial.",
